                            <comment id="12411534" author="gawor@mcs.anl.gov" created="Sat, 4 Mar 2006 03:36:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Created an attachment (id=17831)&lt;br/&gt;
Patch for FileValidatorTest&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12411535" author="gawor@mcs.anl.gov" created="Sat, 4 Mar 2006 03:38:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Btw, the following test cases for DateValidatorTest fail:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;testDefaultDateFormatValidate&lt;br/&gt;
testDefaultTimeFormatValidate&lt;br/&gt;
testDefaultDateTimeFormatValidate&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12411536" author="bayard" created="Wed, 8 Mar 2006 15:13:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed the 3 datetime ones by specifying specific dateformats.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;One still errors for me - which is bizarre as I don&apos;t see how it&apos;s turning&lt;br/&gt;
23-Dec-2003 into 2003-12-22.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12411537" author="gawor@mcs.anl.gov" created="Thu, 9 Mar 2006 01:28:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The problem disappears when the test functions do not reuse the &apos;YYYY_MM_YY&apos; &lt;br/&gt;
DateFormat instance. Creating a new DateFormat instance for each test method &lt;br/&gt;
fixed the problem for me.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12411538" author="roxspring" created="Tue, 21 Mar 2006 07:00:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Could comment #3 be explained by java applying some daylight savings logic?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Just an idea.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12415176" author="bayard" created="Thu, 8 Jun 2006 00:21:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Have applied the idea of creating a new instance. Newbieish as it sounds to blame the JDK, this definitely looks like a bug in SimpleDateFormat. Happens in both 1.4.2 and 1.5.0 on my Apple.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;svn ci -m &quot;Modifying the test so it creates a new format object rather than reusing the static one. For s&lt;br/&gt;
ome reason it gives the wrong response and it&apos;s hard to see why given that it works for other methods and JUnit is single threaded. This is discussed in CLI&lt;br/&gt;
-40&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
Sending        src/test/org/apache/commons/cli2/validation/DateValidatorTest.java&lt;br/&gt;
Transmitting file data .&lt;br/&gt;
Committed revision 412456.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12415177" author="bayard" created="Thu, 8 Jun 2006 00:26:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve also applied the patch for the File test.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; svn ci -m &quot;Applying patch in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CLI-40&quot; title=&quot;DateValidatorTest &amp;amp; FileValidatorTest problems&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CLI-40&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CLI-40&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; that avoids the test from failing sometimes on Windows&quot; src/test/org/vapache/commons/cli2/validation/FileValidatorTest.java&lt;br/&gt;
Sending        src/test/org/apache/commons/cli2/validation/FileValidatorTest.java&lt;br/&gt;
Transmitting file data .&lt;br/&gt;
Committed revision 412457.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
